text.section:
Immunity of the State is not waived under § 12-104 of the State Government Article for:
Punitive damages;
Interest before judgment;
A claim that arises from the combatant activities of the State Militia during a state of emergency;
Any tortious act or omission of State personnel that:
Is not within the scope of the public duties of the State personnel; or
Is made with malice or gross negligence;
A claim by an individual arising from a single incident or occurrence that exceeds $200,000; or
A cause of action that law specifically prohibits.
